<h2>Scarab Administration</h2>

<p>
This is the new administrative piece of Scarab (to replace Flux). At this
point, a lot of the underlying 'action' code is a rip off of the 'Flux'
code. This was done for a number of reasons:
<ol>
  <li> the current user admin using Flux does not look like the rest of
       Scarab; though this is fixed simply by modifying the templates </li>
  <li> ultimately the goal is to remove Flux from Scarab as the Flux 'action
       code' doesn't support the feel that would make it function similar to
       the rest of Scarab </li>
  <li> if the user piece is ever gonna get done, it will be more easily
       picked up if there is a jump point to start at within Scarab </li>
</ol>
</p>

<p>
The following pieces are still using Flux in some manner or another:
<ul>
  <li> Role admin </li>
  <li> Group admin </li>
  <li> Permission admin </li>
</ul>
</p>

<p>
The following are some other things to do (in no particular order):
<ul>
 <li> on 'User Management' pass the search info forward, so that if a user presses cancel it takes them back to the last search (rather than an empty search) </li>
</ul>
</p>

